(If deemed inadvisable to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the Tapeta Course at One Mile and One Sixteenth) (Rail at 28 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOOKINASSAH raced off the pace two and three wide, closed outside and was up in deep stretch. PHOBIA steadied early, advanced three wide around the first turn, pressed two wide down the backstretch and around the far turn, took the lead in midstretch, put away the pace rival leaving the eighth pole but could not withstand the winner. GENTLEMAN GERRY broke awkwardly, checked not long after, raced off the pace two wide, steadied late on the first turn, continued two and three wide off the pace, steadied again nearing the quarter pole then rallied between foes to gain the show late. ROUGH AND ROWDY trailed inside, angled four wide nearing the quarter pole, swung six wide in upper stretch and rallied belatedly. NORFIE broke inwardly, raced three and four wide and never threatened. LIEUTENANT JACK saved ground and failed to menace. MASTER OOGWAY set the pace along the rail to midstretch then tired. FABLED PRINCE chased the pace two wide and came up empty in the lane. FATIH prompted the pace two wide around the first turn, chased inside around the far turn and had little left for the drive.
